This weekend’s tournament, which follows the Nairobi leg held at Royal Nairobi Golf Club three weeks ago, has attracted over 150 players who besides the home players, include members of the Sunset Golfing Society from various clubs in Nairobi such as Royal, Karen, Vet Lab, Kenya Railway Golf Club and Muthaiga Golf Club. Also drawn is Mombasa Golf Club captain Wilfred Achila.





Leading the members from the Nairobi based clubs will be the Society’s chairman Abel Munda, and the Captain Sylvester Odhiambo. The line-up also includes Barth Ragalo, Victor Kidiwa, Ceasar Handa and Hesbon Odumbe all from Royal.
From Muthaiga, will be Maurice Kanjejo, James Ondigo and Philip Ochola, with Pat Odima and Paul Orawo coming from Vet Lab and Kenya Railway Golf Clubs. From Karen will be Isaac Awuondo and Irene Auma among others.
This year, the Mombasa edition had to be cancelled because of the pandemic though the society captain Sylvester Odhiambo said the event may be held next year if the current Covid-19 situation improves.
Odhiambo thanked all the sponsors who have continued supporting the society despite the current economic situation. Besides its key role of encouraging residents of the Nyanza region to take up the game of golf, the society has over the past decade been involving in supporting needy high school students.



