Best condition
Meanwhile at Nakuru Golf Club, the club chairman Stephen Kihumba is hosting the Chairman’s Prize being sponsored by Crown Paints who have also been sponsoring the Extreme Golf series.
Kihumba says this year’s event is in honour of the health workers in the county and country as a whole. He said the proceeds from this weekend’s tournament will go to the Nakuru Hospice.
“Nakuru Golf Club members would like to give a well-deserved kudos to our health workers who gave all they had and continue to risk their lives to keep us healthy. They have worked tirelessly since the first case of Covid-19  was reported in Kenya,’’ said Kihumba.
He said the par 73 course was currently in its best condition and all set for the field of 160 who are expected to battle it out for an array of prizes. The Chairman said a hole-in-one prize of paints voucher worth Sh100,000 at the scenic par three-17th hole will be at stake during the day.
The tournament comes less than a week after the successful Junior tournament which attracted a field for over 100 juniors some of whom will be in action during the weekend.





Away in Nyeri, over 100 were drawn for the 39th edition of the Sana Nagata trophy while at Nanyuki Sports Club, it will be the turn of the Wellspring Chemistry which comes back to back after the Chairman’s Prize.



